Title: Review classification
Description: You will see a review describing a business. Your task is to decide which of the business types most closely matches the business described in the review.

Jill had been doing my hair for years. She has always done a great job. And I don't think I know a nicer person.

She also cut my young sons hair (until he wanted to go to daddy's barber). She always did a wonderful job.
Input.text_59: I highly recommend Shelby for vivid colors! She did amazing and fun colors on my hair, I now have Unicorn hair and I LOVE it! I am so thrilled with the colors! She is professional and you can tell she loves to do color. If you are wanting fun hair, see Shelby!
Input.text_60: For those Crossfit customers that are interested in trying this gym, go ELSEWHERE!  If you're expecting not to pay a dime after you've tried to redeem your groupon with them, they will charge you an ADDITIONAL $80 if you aren't an experienced Crossfit athlete.  I'd like to also mention that the owner was extremely rude!
Input.text_61:
Jon, trainer, did a great job explaining the session workout. He kept the group on point and motivated. Great Endurance Workout!!!

The facility was in great shape, clean and laid out perfectly.

I will definitely be back the next time I am in the Ballantyne area and recommend it to my friends and FedEx work peers.
Input.text_62: I worked with Sarah yesterday to do a balayage (sp?). I absolutely love it and have been getting compliments non-stop. Sarah was amazing to work with - she made the process as enjoyable as possible and was quick and efficient. I will definitely be returning to this salon and have recommended it to a few family and friends already.
Input.text_63: The store is very nice and clean. The layout of the store is a bit confusing because it has a variety of home goods, men, woman and shoes. I couldn't find my size for shoes though, they don't carry 11's. :(
Input.text_64: Guy in the middle does not know how to cut and makes excuses for his mistakes. Focus on the haircut and stop chitchatting. Needs practice. Why would you ever let anyone get off your chair with such a bad hair cut smh you sad my boy. Never going back there
Input.text_65:
This is a great gym, and I go quite often, BUT
some of the TVs in the eclipticals have been broken for weeks. I mentioned this to management and they say they will get them fixed. But they don't follow through. It is frustrating, because I wanted to rate them higher.
Input.text_66: I never write reviews but Robert had such great customer service I had too. My experience at oasis was A1, they fixed a crack in my windshield in no time! Also worked through my insurance so it was free! I also got my car washed there which was also great! They have a lifetime customer!
Input.text_67: My daughter earned her black belt here. She feels she was better prepared for success at Harvard University because of the self discipline and control learned here. Now my other children are working towards their goals. We love the Christian Karate taught here and feel blessed that we found Shehan Smith. We highly recommend him.
Input.text_68: LOVE THIS PLACE ! , Kylie is very professional and caring and makes great effort to make my experience as comfortable as possible,very relaxing and comfortable environment ,and the most important things is that the result are unbelievable!!!!!!!!I HIGHLY RECOMMEND TO GO THERE !!!!!
Input.text_69: This is a "Super Sport" but they do not offer towel service. Keep that in mind especially if you are travelling like me and expect that "Super Sport" benefit. Also, not in the best area of town. I suggest going to the Summerlin location instead or really just go to LVAC.
Input.text_70: My experience with this shop was very negative. High pressure selling and didn't end up with what I really wanted. The owner was also offering discounts if you proved you had written a positive review online. It's interesting that despite this incentive the Yelp reviews are mostly negative - just speaks to how bad this place is!!
Input.text_71: What a store! I had so much fun here. I bought some really nice things that people noticed instantly. I was able to wear them to a VIP party that night, and people thought I was wearing something much more expensive than it was!
Input.text_72: Oh my goodness where do I start? This has been the best exercise experience I've had. All the trainers are super friendly and encouraging. I usually go to the 8:45 am class with Marty who is so sweet, fun, and is always cracking jokes to make working out actually fun.
Input.text_73:
I really like how the receptionist briefly describes each masseuse's type of massage when making appointments. I'll choose deep tissue over relaxing massage 100% of the time!

The masseuses also seem to stay here for years, which says a lot for the place.

I was very very happy with my half-hour neck and shoulders massage.
Input.text_74: I'm very satisfied with the professionalism of the instructors in this Taewkwondo School. They treated my kids very well, and they taught them good habits. Martial arts is very important for kids if it's done by the right experts. I highly recommend this School.
Input.text_75: Marty is terrific and the gym has a great selection of equipment for all levels. Enjoyed training with Marty while in town for a few days for a conference. Great workout. Would come back weekly to train if I lived in Scottsdale.
Input.text_76: A hidden jewel where class sizes are guaranteed to be small and intimate. You'll feel a part of the community here and the owner is one of the nicest human beings around. It feels great to support a small local business.
Input.text_77: This place is not clean! They do not use disposable liners and i got foot fungus... or whatever you call, just nasty, never ever ever had problems... I visited dermatology office and obviously i got it from this nail salon!!! Now i spent so much money on prescription and non prescription creams... I deeply regret of going there...
Input.text_78: I want to provide an update on my previous review. I was able to meet with Rachael to go over my billing concerns and reach a positive outcome. I feel Arizona Centers for Digestive Health is making a sincere effort to help resolve any issues with their clients.
Input.text_79: I started both my girls with Desert Swim School since they were 1 (now 4 and 2) and have been so happy with their progress and results. The teachers are fantastic and the owner Janice has been phenomenal with both my girls! I highly recommend!
Input.text_80: Best location! I love the front desk personnel they are the best, always super nice. This location is smeller than the other 2 I've visited but they have tanning beds and other things that other locations don't offer. Special thank you to Nyat for being very gentle and attentive, I'll be back!
Input.text_81: I can't rave enough about this place! Everything the sell is adorable! I got a ton of jewelry there & it's so reasonably priced. The workers are also great and friendly, super helpful! Clothes I think I are a little pricey but it's a boutique so I expect that. 100% will be going back!
Input.text_82: I have been going to this shop for over 20 years. Started with Margaret then to Kissi and now with Kari. Love all of them. Amazing job on my nails each and every time! Great designs, great customer service love all the ladies in here.
Input.text_83: Maintenance is a joke.  My babysitter lives here and her AC hasn't been repaired.  They took two weeks to fix it and this time it's been broke for 4 days.   The property manager is very unprofessional and does not care about the tenants.  She needs to be replaced immediately.
Input.text_84: Dr Leonetti, and his staff are very professional, compassionate and knowledgeable. I would highly recommend this office to anyone. Diana greets you as soon and you come in and is very kind and quick to get you into to be seen. You will not be disappointed going here.
Input.text_85:
Amazing Salon!
Incredible service! I'm very picky about my nails and the way it's done, and this salon does the best job. I've been going to this place for 6 months now.
Reasonable Prices.
Definitely recommend!
10/10
Input.text_86: If we lived here, we would be new clients!  Well, my boyfriend would.   He couldn't stop raving about his cut and the hot towel!  His hair did look good and he was impressed with the straight razor used on the back of his neck.  Nice place.
Input.text_87: Nail Polished started chipping off that very same day and I was not doing anything that would make that happen. Very Disappointed since I was traveling the next day and did not have time to get them redone. :( Would not go back.
Input.text_88: Better than Scottsdale salons! I got the best haircut of my life from Julie Blake. It was a bit funky but not over the top. She is amazing. The location is not spectacular but why go to a mediocre salon in Scottsdale when you can go to an amazing salon in maybe a not-so-ritzy place.
Input.text_89: DISAPPOINTING !!!!! I don't know where to start !!!! Dirty room, not a spa !!!! I was there for a full 2 hours for mani-pedi...Very poor work, unprofessional, not friendly at all !!! Total waist of time & money !!! Don't go there !!! Ask your 5 year old to do your nails....I'm sure they will look better !!!
Input.text_90: I can not say enough beautiful things about Shannon! She truly has an amazing gift. My experiences with her have been wonderful and she has brought me so much peace. I'm grateful for the recommendation from a friend about Shannon.
Input.text_91: The staff is unprofessional, rude, and seem to think you are wasting their time. Talk about you as soon as you turn your back. Don't waste your money and look elsewhere! Wish I would have read the reviews before I arrived.
Input.text_92: I love Tammy and Co so much.  Such hard workers who take great pride in their craft.  This is one of the very few places in town where I can get a short ladies' cut that's done correctly each time regardless of which of them cuts my hair.  Worth the wait if there is one.  100% recommend!
Input.text_93: I just recently started working out here and I absolutely love it. This is not a, scream in your face, testosterone driven boxing club. Everyone is like family, the staff remembers everyones names and the workouts are intense! You get a good mixture of boxing technique and a hard workout! I'd definitely recommend this place to anyone.
Input.text_94: Updating my last review.   They have improved perfection.  They have just about finished their upgrades.  They have installed motorized lounge chairs.  Kick up your feet while you watch the movie of choice.  The nice spacious seating does cause limited availability, but you can curb that thought their members services.
Input.text_95: They were all super nice and was in and out within an hour. Only bad part was they don't take Kaiser and when you're from Southern Cal attending ASU, the presents a bit of a problem. Hoping Kaiser will reimburse once I send in the receipts!
Input.text_96: Used for a move out of Gilbert, AZ on recommendation by a friend. Booking was straight fwd and movers were on schedule. Everything was wrapped and loaded carefully ... no damaged or broken items. Final price was same as estimate, no problems with markups or hidden fees. Owners were good people, would definitely recommend.
Input.text_97: Letty is my favorite I will never go see anyone else Ever!!! . She is great at what she does and does it with love,passion, and professionalism. Letty always takes care of my hair needs. Not to mention is always great conversation with her while getting beautiful.
Input.text_98: Very impressed with Mike, completely helped me from the moment I got there and the moment I left. Here is the best part, he is the owner of the place. I was able to select my tux and rent price was not bad at all. Thank you Mike
Input.text_99: All the chiropractors are terrific here - Dr. Alex, Dr. Berger, and Dr. Dollarhide - and the staff is friendly and efficient.
